-(IBAction)TraslateIng01:(id)sender{
    
    textLegenda01.text = @"The year was 1785, talking about the old Puebla, was 3 in the morning when Dame Juliana Dominguez, wife of Don Anastasio Priego, wealthy family and inn owners Priego, began with labor pains and needed to go through midwife, Mrs. Simonita. He ran for his hat, cloak and dagger and asked the maid to be preparing everything for childbirth while he returned with the midwife. It was a rainy and stormy night, why they wanted to go with his assistants, also because the wee hours always been conducive to assaults and murders. Don Anastasio did not want the company of anyone and only went to the parish of Analco, which at that time was heading towards the cemetery of St. Thomas Street, now known as 5 East. For the dark of the night was lit with an oil lamp when he surprised a guy who energetically and impolite drew his sword and put it in Mr. Priego abdomen while he demanded gold or life . To this, Don Anastasio was always characterized by being skilled in fencing, was so skilled that few challenged, which is why he jumped up and drew his sword with the speed of lightning, plunged into the heart of the assailant, who immediately fell dead. In his haste he had come to where the midwife forgot what happened and came to the home of this to go to his house, obviously told him about what happened to Donna Simonita. They passed the bridge of Ovando, avoiding back in the same direction, crossed the square of Analco and came back to the inn. They arrived just in time to receive a pair of twins. Following his work, Mr. Anastasio joined the midwife again, more than courtesy, was to return to the scene where he found the corpse surrounded by onlookers who prayed for his soul.";
    
}
-(IBAction)TraslateIng02:(id)sender{
    
    textLegenda02.text = @"Earlier, in what were the first buildings in the city, was a nunnery, I'm talking early to mid last century. In this convent housed women with unwanted pregnancies, for women to become nuns at the same time and some never hear about them again. Over the years, when these facilities were remodeled since the convent was not there, lay down very thick walls, once took up to one meter wide, to the surprise, they found skeletons of newborns. It is said that the nuns never knew emparedaban for them because they were God's unwanted children. In these areas had as extensive tunnels reaching to the Metropolitan Cathedral in Hermosillo. These tunnels were sealed and never wanted to inform the public, which was totally impossible, but sealed the tunnels, are still there. But at night the street Serdan, feel a very strange, and even heard moans, cries or looks very strange people walking there alone, pregnant beautiful women walking alone through the center of the city at night is extremely dangerous, are said to be the souls of women who died there, and yelling are of babies who died within the walls of the convent. Today there is housed a bank, offices of the National Institute of Adult Education and the Institute Soria.";
    
