}
-(IBAction)TraslateIng09:(id)sender{
    
    textLegenda09.text = @"At night in the mountains of Mexico State fireballs are jumping from one tree to another as they move quietly to the village. I said near the town of San Juan, Mexico, a man driving his truck down the road late in the morning suddenly collided with a female figure and the spirit of it went through the whole body hit it with his truck. The man, between confused and upset, she got out of the cab to assist the woman he thought he had hit, but instead found a large black bat, badly wounded. He decided to take it and give it to a vet, cast him in the back of the truck, the trailer where he had the entire load. After a few minutes, while driving, began to hear noises, screams and many blows to the back of the truck. He immediately stopped the truck, lower back of the cab and went to see what happened in the trailer. When you open the cargo door the noise stopped. The bat was gone and in its place appeared the body of a dead woman. If you get panicky read it, I argued the witness history at the time, had been a direct participant of one of them. Imagine the look on his face as he recounted it to me all along with a small wood burning fireplace with four and the firelight only served us light to see our faces in that dark night. It was a very eerie experience I remember traveling by land from Mexico.";
    
}
-(IBAction)TraslateIng10:(id)sender{
    
    textLegenda10.text = @"The Huichol were tired of eating things that did not like. They wanted something they could eat every day, but in different ways. A young Huichol heard of corn and its famous mets, omelets, chilaquiles, and tortilla soup prepared with rice. But corn was far away on the other side of the mountain. That did not discourage him and stood up. Soon after he saw a line of ants and how he knew that some of them were the keepers of corn, followed. But when the young man slept, ants, without any problem, devoured all his clothes, leaving him alone with his bow and arrows. Without clothes and hungry Huichol began to regret. Then a bird landed on a nearby tree. The young man pointed his bow on it, but the bird scolded him and told him she was the mother of corn. He invited him to follow it to the House of Corn where she would authorize take whatever he wanted. In the House of Corn were five beautiful maidens, daughters of the Mother of Corn: Corn White Corn Blue, Yellow Corn, Corn Cob Red and Black. Blue Corn was enchanted with her beauty and sweetness. They married and returned to the Huichol village. Since he was not even home, slept one time in a place dedicated to the gods. Then, as if by magic, the home of the newlyweds heads filled every day of the decorated like flowers. People came from everywhere for Blue Corn ears were offered in abundance. The beautiful wife taught her husband to plant corn and crop care. By learning what delights offered this new food, the animals tried to rob him. Blue Corn taught the people to put fire around crops to scare the beasts in search of tender ears. The Elders say that Blue Corn, having taught all she knew, she was ground and that is how the men met the excellent atole, a hot drink that is made from corn.";
    
}
-(IBAction)TraslateIng11:(id)sender{
    
    textLegenda11.text = @"Long ago, on the road to the Rumorosa, a trucker drove at full speed towards Mexicali, because his wife was about to give birth and wanted to get home quickly, took money for what is offered, but when he taking a dangerous curve lost control and crashed into some rocks. The driver got out of the trailer all stunned, looked at his body and was glad to learn that it had not happened. Then waited for someone to pass to help him or take him to the city, but no long crossed those hills. The man fell asleep and when he awoke he was surprised to see all dark; not understand what happened so I decided to walk, walked and walked, advanced a good distance, I knew the noisy output was near and yet when he realized was found in the same place of the accident ... Three days later found the truck but the driver, it was not heard anything. Until once, years later, a boy who was driving a truck was stopped because a man beckoned. Friend, my name is Francisco Vazquez and badly need my wife to get some money because it will have a child. I can not go, my trailer broke down and I can not stop here. -Yes, sir, we will gladly take it, 'said the boy just tell me where his wife lives. The man handed him a paper they wrote down his address and the name of his wife. On parting, the young man felt a chill run down his back, because when shaking hands, Mr. were as cold as a corpse. The boy did not care, got into his trailer and headed to Mexicali. The next day, went looking for the lady but did not find it, someone said he no longer lived there, who had long changed. without giving up, asked in several places until, by the signs of the paper, an old woman told him where he lived. to get rapped on the door and waited for them to open. - Tell me young man? Asked the lady. -Excuse me, here lives the wife of Mr. Francisco Vázquez? -Me-she answered what you want? -Yesterday on the road, her husband asked me to bring this money, because he broke the trailer ... - No way! Mrs. interrupted him covering his mouth. My husband died five years ago. The boy shook his legs, he left money to the lady, who began to mourn, and went to his house all scared. When he arrived, the door had scarcely closed when he found against the truck driver jumped the road and frightened, felt a strange force inside him. - Thanks, dude! 'Said the dead in a hollow voice, as he disappeared. The boy could hear the beating of your heart and it took a while to recover from the shock. thereafter, by talking with friends, he learned that the truck driver and he had appeared to men, they had not fulfilled the task of the dead, so they dried up the body to look like skeletons.";
    
}
-(IBAction)TraslateIng12:(id)sender{
    
    textLegenda12.text = @"'It is said that here at Mexicali, the devil made an appearance in a popular nightclub for the year 1960, causing panic among those present, be something in the media to spread, causing the youth of that time The think twice before going to dance .... ' Back in the 60's down the street 11, began to spread the nightclubs, where there was music, alcoholic beverages of various kinds and in large quantities where partying young clientele grew into account. The boys invited the girls or their girlfriends to these places to dance all night, get drunk and play big. The most famous nightclubs of that time were La Ronda, Waikiki and Los Cocos. Many of our parents, when young, were the places we used to go. One night, it turns out that in Los Cocos, while everyone was having a good time, came a boy, hopeless almost suffocated crying - appeared in the Round the Devil! -. Naturally, no one believed him (it was thought that the guy had taken over), but seeing that Round hysterical people out, it caused an uproar. Some went quickly to their homes, others were curious to La Ronda to see and hear other people's event. What people who were present, they said, was that a very elegant and handsome, he took a girl to dance, she accepted and dancing lasted many hours, and when it struck 12 midnight, that person began to change, horns sticking out, changing your skin tone and smell of sulfur, giving off smoke, some say a big storm broke out in there and leaving the girl fainted, others say it took her. When this was going on, hysteria was allowed to come, everyone was terrified fleeing Round, the place was left alone when all this happened, we all panicked. The rumor became general among the population Mexicali, causing decreased the boom too had those nightclubs, the alleged apparition of the devil ....... * This legend has told me many people who used to go to those places in the 60's, I decided to investigate and find out more about it, finding out something very interesting. Turns out to those places, was always a boy who liked to drink and dance, was well known and everyone called him 'the devil'. That night, where presumably the devil appeared, what really happened was that there was a great fight between several people and that young man 'the devil' was who led the entire lawsuit, and they all said that 'the devil' was in the round and caused a major scandal, the trouble is that what people understand, or want to understand ... it was something else .....";
    
}


